OL,7,FOther prominent nationalists to
OL,8,Freceive small chips include Margo
OL,9,FMacDonald and Winnie Ewing ` who had
OL,10,Fher piece fashioned into the centre of
OL,11,Fa brooch she once wore to an interview
OL,12,Fwith the BBC's David Frost.
OL,14,FCanadian journalist Dick Sanburn
OL,15,Freceived chip number 25 in 1951 and
OL,16,Fproudly kept it behind his desk at the
OL,17,FCalgary Herald. He said the fragments
OL,18,Fwere "carefully numbered and recorded
OL,19,Fto prevent a flood of fakes".
